<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File 838.77/102.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My telegram of September 25. The Haitian Government has today served
                            notice of foreclosure on the National Railroad Company of Haiti for
                            non-compliance with Article 11 of the railroad contract and given notice
                            of the adjudication of the property on December 28. The Haitian
                            Government has also notified claim for damages caused the Government and
                            public by the suspension of operation, and has appointed an arbitrator
                            on its part for examination of this last claim.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>